  "description": "An overnight EEG-fMRI study conducted at the National Institutes of Health examining sleep physiology through simultaneous electroencephalography and functional magnetic resonance imaging. Subjects underwent two consecutive nights of approximately 8-hour scanning sessions with randomized arousal stimuli administered 8 times each night. This pilot study establishes methodology for investigating the neural correlates of sleep and arousal responses.",
  "methods_description": "Subjects were scanned for two consecutive nights for approximately 8 hours using simultaneous EEG-fMRI acquisition. Subjects were aroused at random intervals 8 times each night.",
